# Solo Workflow — local SQLite, no sync hub

> **Project:** {{ .ProjectPrefix }}
> **Generated by:** mtix {{ .Version }}
> **Workflow audience:** individual contributors, pre-team adoption.

> **Trust banner.** The sync hub is a replication mechanism, not a
> tenancy boundary. Anyone with the hub DSN can read every event ever
> pushed. This solo workflow does not use a sync hub, but the same
> trust assumption applies the moment you opt into one — read
> [docs/SECURITY-MODEL.md](../SECURITY-MODEL.md) before adding teammates.

This is the default mtix mode. One developer, one machine, one SQLite
database under `.mtix/data/mtix.db`. Sync between machines (your laptop
and your desktop, say) is via the git-tracked `.mtix/tasks.json` snapshot.

You should pick this workflow if you are a single developer or
evaluating mtix before bringing a team in. When you add even one
collaborator who needs to mutate tasks, move to the
[small-team workflow](small-team.md) — concurrent SQLite writers across
machines is not a supported topology.

---

## Setup steps

1. Install mtix: `go install github.com/hyper-swe/mtix/cmd/mtix@latest`.
2. Initialize the project from your repo root: `mtix init`. This creates
   `.mtix/data/mtix.db` and the documentation set.
3. Verify `.mtix/data/` is **not** in `.gitignore`. SQLite is tracked
   alongside the snapshot file so a fresh clone has a working store.
4. Create your first task: `mtix create --title "Bootstrap the codebase"`.
5. Optional: install the bundled Claude Code skills with
   `mtix plugin install claude-code` so your IDE agent picks them up.

