## Failure modes

| What can go wrong | How mtix behaves | What you do |
|---|---|---|
| `.mtix/data/mtix.db` corrupted | Read/write fails with a clear error | Restore from `.mtix/tasks.json` via `mtix import`; commit a fresh snapshot |
| Two agents on same machine race a write | SQLite WAL + busy_timeout serialize writes | No action; this is the supported concurrent topology for solo mode |
| **Hub unreachable** | N/A — solo mode does not use a sync hub | Switch to small-team workflow before adding remote collaborators |
| **Hook bypassed** (`git push --no-verify`) | tasks.json may lag the DB | Re-export with `mtix export` and commit |
| **Schema mismatch** after upgrade | Startup migration runs automatically; failure aborts | `mtix verify`, then re-run; report a bug if migration loops |
| **Queue full** | N/A — sync queue is empty in solo mode | Not applicable to solo mode |
| **Lost laptop** | The git-tracked `.mtix/tasks.json` is your only off-machine copy | Restore from a fresh clone via `mtix import` — see "Disaster recovery" below |
| **Divergent history** | N/A — solo mode has only one source of events | Not applicable to solo mode |

---

## Trust boundary

**What this workflow protects against:**

- Local data loss — `.mtix/tasks.json` snapshot in git history is your DR.
- Concurrent agent corruption on one machine — SQLite WAL handles it.
- SQL injection in filter inputs — all queries are parameterized.

**What this workflow does NOT protect against:**

- A teammate concurrently editing the same SQLite file from another
  machine — solo mode is single-machine. Use small-team for that.
- Loss of your laptop without a recent push — the `.mtix/tasks.json`
  in git is your only off-machine copy.
- Tampering with the local SQLite file by anything running on your
  machine. Solo mode trusts the local machine fully.

---

## Disaster recovery

Solo DR is git-driven and intentionally minimal:

1. Clone the repo to a new machine.
2. Run `mtix init` if `.mtix/data/mtix.db` is missing.
3. Run `mtix import .mtix/tasks.json` to rebuild the SQLite store from
   the last committed snapshot.
4. Verify with `mtix list --status open`.

For richer DR (sync hub backup + immutable cold storage), see the
[safety-critical workflow](safety-critical.md), which uses the BYO
Postgres sync hub and documents the full restore procedure.

